line_1: "Nature t' adorn thy name with Fortune vies,
line_2: " At thy command the unyielding rebel dies;

line_1: And Art, by Judgment form'd, with Nature vies.
line_2: BUT, spight of all defects, his glories rise;

line_1: Responsive now with their soft voice she vies,
line_2: Or, while her hand the curious needle plies,

line_1: For this the painter's art with nature vies,
line_2: And bids the visionary saint arise;

line_1: Now with Lord Trinket in his carriage vies;
line_2: To ape the courtly fop in vain he tries;
